# Global shortcuts

## Backup ritual

| Operator says | Agent action |
|---------------|--------------|
| **`backup project`**, **`create backup`**, **`backup`** | Interactive ritual — **AskQuestion** buttons each step ([CURSOR.md](../custom-scriptz/backup-system/CURSOR.md), [interactive-workflows.mdc](./interactive-workflows.mdc)) |
| **`backup quick`**, **`backup project quick`** | **Non-interactive:** run `npm run msc:backup:quick` from repo root — no questions, no note prompt |
| **`backup full`**, **`backup project full`** | **Non-interactive:** run `npm run msc:backup:quick:full` from repo root — no questions, no note prompt |

Quick commands use default backup root (`G:\Cursor_Project_BackUpz\MyStudioChannel`), auto-suggest next `msc-website-v1-*` folder, and `--yes`.

After quick backup completes, report destination path and `.cursor/BackUp-Notez.md`.

## Push website live

| Operator says | Agent action |
|---------------|--------------|
| **`push website live`**, **`push it live`**, **`push site live`**, **`deploy live`** | Run **Push Website Live** playbook ([`.cursor/prompts/Push-Website-Live.md`](../prompts/Push-Website-Live.md)) — preflight → FTPS deploy → hPanel restart gate → `verify:live` + `verify:live:version` |

**Local command:** `npm run push:website:live` (dry-run: `npm run push:website:live -- --dry-run`).

**Deployment zips:** save to `zips/` only — `MyStudioChannel-v4-deploy-YYYYMMDD-HHmmss.zip` (never repo parent folder).
